'''Birgid''' (also known as Birked, Birguid, Birkit, Birqed, Kajjara, Murgi, Murgi Birked) is an [[Extinct language|extinct]] [[Nubian language]] that was spoken in western [[Sudan]], north of the city of [[Nyala, Sudan|Nyala]] in [[Darfur]]. Canadian linguist Thelwall mentions his last contact with old speakers of Birgid in 1972.

