'''Michael Rotohiko Jones''' {{post-nominals|country=NZL|CBE|MM}} (14 September 1895 – 24 January 1978) was a New Zealand interpreter, land agent, sportsman, private secretary, public administrator and broadcaster. Of [[Māori people|Māori]] descent, he identified with the [[Ngāti Maniapoto]] [[iwi]]. He was born in [[Poro-o-Tarao]], [[King Country]], New Zealand, on 14 September 1895.<ref name="DNZB Jones">{{DNZB|title=Michael Rotohiko Jones|first= Reimana Rotohiko|last= Jones|id=4j10|accessdate=4 February 2012}}</ref>
In the [[1961 New Year Honours (New Zealand)|1961 New Year Honours]], Jones was appointed an [[Order of the British Empire|Officer of the Order of the British Empire]] for services to the [[Māori people]].<ref>{{London Gazette |issue=42233 |date=31 December 1960 |page=8928 |supp=y }}</ref> In the [[1975 Birthday Honours]], he was promoted to [[Commander of the Order of the British Empire]], again for services to the Māori people.<ref>{{London Gazette |date=6 June 1975 |supp=y |issue=46595 |page=7406 }}</ref>
