The [[Paper Mate]] PhD Multi is a [[pen]]/[[pencil]]/[[stylus]] combination. The PhD series of pens and pencils have been specifically designed for durability and comfort, notably with a unique ergonomic, cushioned triangular grip that is endorsed by the [[American Physical Therapy Association]].<ref>http://www.apta.org/AM/Template.cfm?Section=Endorsed_Products&Template=/CM/HTMLDisplay.cfm&ContentID=79608{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The PhD series of pens also distinguishes itself from most other Paper mate products by having a sturdier, higher-quality design.<ref>http://www.papermate.com/Pages/products.aspx</ref>

==Mechanics and Design==
The modes of the pen (black ink), pencil (0.5mm [[Pencil lead|lead]]), stylus for a [[Resistive touchscreen|touchscreen]] device (orange blunt plastic tip), and retracting the pen are engaged by turning the barrel. A button at the top releases the lead when pressed, and the button's cap can be removed to reveal an [[eraser]].  The PhD is also available with a red ink cartridge in place of the PDA stylus.

== Replacement and Maintenance ==
Since [[Paper Mate]] has no signification on replacement parts and model numbers, there have been owners who have done modifications with other pen ink cartridges. These owners would take other [[Paper Mate]] ballpoint stick pens and trim their cartridges with the original cartridges. In addition, you can use [[Paper Mate]]'s Inkjoy 100 RT substitute refills with the same process of trimming.

